import pandas as pd
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer
from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity
In [32]:
vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer()
In [33]:
positive_example = "Good Quality"
In [35]:
df['summary'] = df['overall'].apply(lambda x: 'good' if x > 2 else 'bad')
In [37]:
tfidf_matrix = vectorizer.fit_transform(df['summary'].tolist() + [positive_example])  #Term Freq. inverse Doc Freq
In [38]:
# Separate the TF-IDF vectors
summary_tfidf = tfidf_matrix[:-1]
positive_tfidf = tfidf_matrix[-1]
In [39]:
# Compute cosine similarity
cosine_similarities = cosine_similarity(summary_tfidf, positive_tfidf.reshape(1, -1))
In [40]:
# Add cosine similarity classification
df['cosine_classification'] = ['good' if sim > 0 else 'bad' for sim in cosine_similarities]
In [42]:
# Add score-based classification
df['score_classification'] = ['good' if score > 2 else 'bad' for score in df['overall']]
In [43]:
# Final classification in the summary column based on score, and handle empty summaries
df['summary_classification'] = df.apply(
    lambda row: row['score_classification'] if row['summary'] == '' else row['cosine_classification'], axis=1
)

In [51]:
import re
In [52]:
num_urls_regExp = re.compile(r'https?:\/\/t\.co\/\w+')
char_regExp = re.compile(r'[,:|?]')
quoteHtml_regExp = re.compile(r'(&#8220;)|(&#8221;)')
andHtml_regExp = re.compile(r'(&amp;)')
emo_happy = re.compile(r'(&#128515;)|(&#128514;)')  # Pattern for happy emojis
html_tags_regExp = re.compile(r'<[^>]*>')
In [53]:
def clean_text(text):
    text = re.sub(num_urls_regExp, '', text)               # Remove URLs
    text = re.sub(andHtml_regExp, 'and', text)            # Replace HTML & with 'and'
    text = re.sub(char_regExp, ' ', text)                 # Remove special characters ,:|?
    text = re.sub(quoteHtml_regExp, '', text)             # Remove HTML quotes
    text = re.sub(html_tags_regExp, '', text)             # Remove HTML tags
    text = text.lower()                                   # Convert to lowercase
    text = re.sub(emo_happy, 'happy', text)               # Replace happy emojis with 'happy'
    text = " ".join(text.split())                         # Remove extra spaces
    return text

from collections import Counter
import re
In [82]:
# Function to clean the text
def clean_text(text):
    text = text.lower()
    text = re.sub(r'\b\w{1,2}\b', '', text)  # remove short words
    text = re.sub(r'\s+', ' ', text)  # remove extra spaces
    text = re.sub(r'[^\w\s]', '', text)  # remove punctuation
    return text
